<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910204-0184</DOCNO><DOCID>910204-0184.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Benton Oil andamp; Gas Co.:   Possible Joint Venture Set   For Study in Soviet Union</HL><DATE>02/04/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   BNTN FREST</CO><IN>OIL EQUIPMENT AND SERVICES (OIE)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)PETROLEUM (PET)</IN><LP>   Benton Oil andamp; Gas Co., Ventura, Calif., said it signed aletter of intent to pursue a joint venture to explore,develop and produce oil and natural gas in parts of westernSiberia in the Soviet Union.   The oil and gas production company said the agreement wasmade with the Purneftegasgeologia Industrial Association, thegoverning authority that regulates fields in the area. Theagreement calls for Soviet officials to provide technicalsurveys over the next two to three months.</LP><TEXT>   Afterwards, if both parties &quot;agree to pursue the project,a joint venture will be formed,&quot; the company said.   A Benton spokesman said the letter of intent marks thecompany's first venture into the Soviet Union.</TEXT></DOC>